  "text": "We apply very sparse stable random projections on some MSN Web crawl data. We pick two pairs of words, THIS-HAVE, and SCHOOL-PROGRAM. The data dimension D = 2 [CITATION_1] = 65536. For each word, the ith entry (i = 1 to D) are plotted against the sample size k for each D=100, 500, and 1000. The \"theoretic\" curves were the theoretical variances assuming the data are exactly (instead of asymptotically) stable (see Lemma 2) .",
